.SH SYNOPSIS
function \fBGetCursorType\fR:Word;
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBGetCursorType\fR returns the current cursor type. It is one of the following values:

.TP
.B crHidden
Hide cursor
.TP
.B crUnderLine
Underline cursor
.TP
.B crBlock
Block cursor
.TP
.B crHalfBlock
Half block cursor
.TP 0
Note that not all drivers support all types of cursors.


